{"metadata":{"title":"Getting Started","modules":[{"name":"Nuke"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Essentials","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/swiftui","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/uikit","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageRequest","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageResponse","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageTask"],"anchor":"Essentials"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about main Nuke features and APIs."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Image Pipeline","type":"heading","anchor":"Image-Pipeline","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" downloads images, caches, and prepares them for display. To load an image, use an async method "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline\/image(for:)-7r8ga"},{"type":"text","text":" returning an image."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let image = try await ImagePipeline.shared.image(for: url)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To get more control over the download, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline\/imageTask(with:)-5z12i"},{"type":"text","text":" to create an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageTask"},{"type":"text","text":" and then access its "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageTask\/image"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageTask\/response","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" to receive the image."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func loadImage() async throws {","    let imageTask = ImagePipeline.shared.imageTask(with: url)","    for await progress in imageTask.progress {","        \/\/ Update progress","    }","    imageView.image = try await imageTask.image","}"]},{"style":"tip","type":"aside","name":"Tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can start by using a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline\/shared","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" pipeline and create a custom one later. To create a custom pipeline, use a convenience ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline\/init(delegate:_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" initializer or one of the pre-defined configurations, such as ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline\/Configuration-swift.struct\/withDataCache","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The documentation uses Async\/Await APIs in the examples, but "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline"},{"type":"text","text":" also has equivalent completion-based and Combine APIs."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Image Request","anchor":"Image-Request"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageRequest"},{"text":" allows you to set image processors, downsample images, change the request priority, and provide other options. See ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageRequest"},{"text":" reference to learn more.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let request = ImageRequest(","    url: URL(string: \"http:\/\/example.com\/image.jpeg\"),","    processors: [.resize(width: 320)],","    priority: .high,","    options: [.reloadIgnoringCachedData]",")","let image = try await pipeline.image(for: request)"]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use built-in processors or create custom ones. Learn more in "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/image-processing"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Tip","style":"tip"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Caching","anchor":"Caching"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Nuke has two cache layers: memory cache and disk cache.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageCache"},{"text":" stores images prepared for display in memory. It uses a fraction of available RAM and automatically removes most cached images when the app goes to the background or receives a memory pressure warning.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For caching data persistently, by default, Nuke uses ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/foundation\/urlcache"},{"text":" with an increased capacity. One of its advantages is HTTP ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.mozilla.org\/en-US\/docs\/Web\/HTTP\/Headers\/Cache-Control"},{"text":" support.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can also replace ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"URLCache"},{"text":" with a custom ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/DataCache"},{"text":" that ignores HTTP ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cache-control"},{"text":" headers using ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline\/Configuration-swift.struct\/withDataCache(name:sizeLimit:)"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["ImagePipeline.shared = ImagePipeline(configuration: .withDataCache)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/DataCache"},{"text":" is faster than ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"URLCache"},{"text":" and provides more control. For example, it can be configured to store processed images using ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline\/Configuration-swift.struct\/dataCachePolicy"},{"text":". The downside is that without HTTP ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cache-control"},{"text":", the images never get validated, and if the URL content changes, the app will continue showing stale data.","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To learn more about caching, see "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/caching"},{"type":"text","text":" section."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Tip","style":"tip"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Performance","anchor":"Performance"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"One of the key Nuke features is performance. It does a lot by default: custom cache laye